The paper deals with visual relationship detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) that involves detecting and describing the interactions between objects in an image. The paper also proposes a deep learning model (Convolutional Neural Network) to address this problem, which falls under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it considers visual relationships as phrases with three components. Finally, the paper deals with image processing (cs.MM) as it involves detecting and localizing objects in an image.
